Reasoning: The paper deals with the development and evaluation of embeddings for medical concepts using word2vec, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of hyperparameters and frequency of concepts, which are relevant to machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the distribution of context words, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
